isciplinary breach\\\" by her entourage, including younger sister Nisha.\", \"from\": 8924, \"to\": 9089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8988, \"end\": 8993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.724819432357236e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Panghal\", \"from\": 8924, \"to\": 8931}, {\"ngram\": \"the 53kg\", \"from\": 8960, \"to\": 8968}, {\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 8997, \"to\": 9005}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"disciplinary breach\", \"from\": 9016, \"to\": 9038}, {\"ngram\": \"her entourage\", \"from\": 9043, \"to\": 9056}, {\"ngram\": \"younger sister\", \"from\": 9068, \"to\": 9082}, {\"ngram\": \"Nisha\", \"from\": 9083, \"to\": 9088}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She had already been knocked out in her quarter-final bout a day earlier, losing 10-0 to Turkey's Zeynep Yetgil.\", \"from\": 9090, \"to\": 9202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9179, \"end\": 9185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"score\": 0.999999946858226, \"rank\": 5.3141760632829925e-08, \"text\": \"Turkey\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Turkey\"}, {\"begin\": 9188, \"end\": 9201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zeynep_Yetgil\", \"score\": 0.9999998803950874, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zeynep Yetgil\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zeynep_Yetgil\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zeynep_Yetgil\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her quarter-final bout\", \"from\": 9126, \"to\": 9148}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Independentcontacted India's chef de mission in Paris, Gagan Narang, with a detailed questionnaire.\", \"from\": 9204, \"to\": 9307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9229, \"end\": 9234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resourc